    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/1080289/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1080289-1.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/1080289/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">Stanley</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2016-12-02"
      class="main-meta">2016-12-02 14:16:40</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_8205310_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  霍普柯克这部作品，看起来归为带学术性的通俗历史写作或科普读物一类可能更合适些。这么说毫无贬低之意，我也不认为哪个比哪个就一定更高。而且全书视野宏大，作者也投入了某种感情，读来不仅有知识上的提升，也令人为之动容。不论是俄罗斯帝国边疆军人的勃勃雄心，还是大英帝...

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">2有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
